&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Levanta is the leading affiliate marketing platform for marketplace sellers, helping Amazon, Shopify and Walmart brands unlock a scalable, cost-effective marketing channel through direct affiliate partnerships. With access to over 70,000 vetted publishers, influencers, affiliates, and media buyers in Levanta’s Creator Marketplace, sellers can drive high-quality external traffic to their stores, control commissions, improve organic search rankings, and benefit from referral kickbacks on sales generated by their affiliates.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for an organized, personable, and social-media-savvy Creator Growth &amp;amp; Marketing Coordinator to join our Creator Team. This is a hybrid role centered on creator acquisition, with meaningful marketing and content responsibilities alongside it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your primary mission is growth: recruiting new creators to Levanta at scale, with a particular focus on creators who can drive revenue across our expanding non-Amazon marketplaces:&amp;nbsp; Walmart, Shopify brands (DTC), and upcoming marketplace partnerships. Amazon is already well-served; the biggest opportunity ahead of us is building deliberate creator supply in these newer channels. You&#39;ll spend a significant part of your time sourcing and reaching out to creators who are already promoting these brands and showing them how to earn more through Levanta.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll work closely with our GTM and automation systems, which handle much of the top-of-funnel volume, enriching leads, sequencing outreach, and managing routine replies. Your role is the human layer on top of that engine: personalizing outreach, handling the more nuanced conversations, and making sure the creators you bring in actually activate. Alongside acquisition, you&#39;ll help own Levanta&#39;s social presence and support the Creator Team&#39;s content and community efforts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Creator Acquisition &amp;amp; Marketplace Growth&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Source and recruit creators across Instagram, TikTok, Facebook, YouTube, and Pinterest, with an emphasis on those driving revenue in non-Amazon categories (Walmart, DTC stores, and upcoming marketplace partnerships)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify creators already promoting these brands and other marketplaces, and run warm outreach showing them how to earn more through Levanta&#39;s higher commission rates&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run targeted outreach campaigns by category and marketplace to fill creator-supply gaps where we have brand demand but thin coverage&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Personalize outreach messaging over email and social based on creator niche, audience size, marketplace focus, and content style&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Encourage existing Levanta creators to expand into new marketplaces, curating product lists and hooks tied to specific brands and campaigns&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage inbound and complex outreach replies that fall outside automated workflows, qualifying, answering questions, and moving creators toward sign-up and activation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow up with interested creators, book meetings with our Creator Managers, and help ensure new creators reach their first post and first attributed sale&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Outreach Operations &amp;amp; Automation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and manage outreach sequences that drive sign-ups to the Levanta platform&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with our GTM engineering function to feed the outreach engine, refine targeting, and build marketplace-specific outreach tracks (e.g., distinct messaging for Walmart vs. other marketplaces vs. DTC)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track outreach activity, response rates, and pipeline progress in our CRM, and share what&#39;s converting&lt;/li&gt;
